## Final Bundle Quality Checklist

Before finalizing, verify:

- The proposal is suitable for splitting.
- The split is based on strategic capability boundaries, not implementation tasks.
- The original strategic opportunity is fully preserved.
- No unrelated opportunity was added.
- Each resulting epic owns exactly one coherent capability.
- Resulting epics minimize overlap.
- Dependency relationships among epics are explicit.
- Each epic is independently meaningful.
- Each epic is grounded in repository reality.
- Each epic is aligned with the projection.
- Each epic stands alone without requiring the original proposal.
- Each epic includes a coherent milestone roadmap.
- Milestones are capability-oriented, not task-oriented.
- Acceptance criteria are auditable.
- Dependencies are explicit and evidence-backed.
- Constraints are explicit and evidence-backed.
- Risks are specific and evidence-backed.
- Repository findings are compressed into strategic grounding.
- Canonical projection vocabulary is preserved.
- No implementation tasks are included.
- No file-level plans are included.
- No roadmap changes are made.
- No roadmap completion context changes are made.
- No projection changes are made.